==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Healthy
<hw>Health"y</hw> <pr>(-⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Healthier</adjf>
<pr>(-⟦icr⟧*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Healthiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Being in a state of
health; enjoying health; hale; sound; free from disease; <as>as, a
<ex>healthy</ex> child; a <ex>healthy</ex> plant.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His mind was now in a firm and <qex>healthy</qex> state.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Evincing health; <as>as, a <ex>healthy</ex> pulse; a
<ex>healthy</ex> complexion.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Conducive to health; wholesome; salubrious;
salutary; <as>as, a <ex>healthy</ex> exercise; a <ex>healthy</ex>
climate.</as></def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Vigorous; sound; hale; salubrious; healthful;
wholesome; salutary.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heam</ent>⟦br⟧
